{"title": "Adventures of Tom Sawyer", "description": "The Adventures of Tom Sawyer (published 1876) is a very well-known and popular story concerning American youth. Mark Twain's lively tale of the scrapes and adventures of boyhood is set in St. Petersburg, Missouri, where Tom Sawyer and his friend Huckleberry Finn have the kinds of adventures many boys can imagine: racing bugs during class, impressing girls, especially Becky Thatcher, with fights and stunts in the schoolyard, getting lost in a cave, and playing pirates on the Mississippi River.<br><br>\nOne of the most famous incidents in the book describes how Tom persuades his friends to do a boring, hateful chore for him: whitewashing (i.e., painting) a fence.<br><br>\nThis was the first novel to be written on a typewriter.<br><br>\n(Summary from Wikipedia)", "duration": 24372, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "9", "name": "Mark Twain"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/tom_sawyer_librivox/tom_sawyer2.jpg", "copyright_year": "1876", "genres": ["Children's Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "John Greenman"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "John Greenman"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Gesine"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Chapters 01 to 02", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/tom_sawyer_librivox/TSawyer_01-02_twain_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1598}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapters 03 to 04", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/tom_sawyer_librivox/TSawyer_03-04_twain_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1978}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapters 05 to 06", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/tom_sawyer_librivox/TSawyer_05-06_twain_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1911}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapters 07 to 08", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/tom_sawyer_librivox/TSawyer_07-08_twain_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1280}, {"section": 5, "title": "Chapters 09 to 10", "readers": [107], "pat